-- Lebanon's Inflation Rate Falls to 3.5% as Health, Communication Costs Drop
-- Massoud A. Derhally
-- 2010-07-21T08:57:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-21/lebanon-s-inflation-rate-falls-to-3-5-as-health-communication-costs-drop.html

          
          
             Lebanonâ€™s inflation rate fell to 3.5
percent in June from 4.9 percent the month before as health and
communication costs declined.  
 Prices dropped 0.8 percent from the previous month, the
 Central Administration of Statistics  said on its  website  today.  
 Health costs fell an annual 3.4 percent and communication
declined 0.3 percent, while water, electricity, gas and other
fuels rose 7.6 percent and education charges increased 9.6
percent, the statistics office said.  
